In [13]:
## Doing ANOVA to check importance of variable with respect to Signal Strength

importantvar = []
for i in df.columns[:-1]:
    a = i + " ~ Signal_Strength"
    mod = ols(a, data = df).fit()
    aov_table = sm.stats.anova_lm(mod, typ = 2)
    if aov_table['PR(>F)'][0] < 0.01:
        importantvar.append([i, aov_table['PR(>F)'][0] ])

## Model tuning to find the best hyperparameters

from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam, SGD, RMSprop, Adadelta, Adagrad

from tensorflow.keras.wrappers.scikit_learn import KerasRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_percentage_error, make_scorer

ftwo_scorer = make_scorer(mean_absolute_percentage_error)

# Function to create model, required for KerasClassifier

## Not tuning on learning rate simply because the compute time increases multifold

def create_model(activation = 'relu', neuron = 10, optimizer = 'adam'):
# create model
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(neuron, activation=activation))
    model.add(Dense(neuron, activation=activation))
    model.add(Dense(1, activation='relu'))
# Compile model
    model.compile(loss='mse', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['mae'])
    return model
# fix random seed for reproducibility
seed = 0
np.random.seed(seed)
# create model
model = KerasRegressor(build_fn=create_model, verbose=0)
# define the grid search parameters
batch_size = [10, 60, 100]
epochs = [20, 50, 100]
neuron = [10,50,100,200]
optimizer = ['SGD', 'Adam']
activation = ['relu','elu','tanh']



param_grid = dict(batch_size=batch_size, epochs=epochs, activation = activation, neuron = neuron, optimizer = optimizer)
grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=model, param_grid=param_grid, n_jobs=-1, cv=3, scoring= ftwo_scorer)
grid_result = grid.fit(X, y)

## summarize results


means = grid_result.cv_results_['mean_test_score']
stds = grid_result.cv_results_['std_test_score']
params = grid_result.cv_results_['params']
for mean, stdev, param in zip(means, stds, params):
    print("%f (%f) with: %r" % (mean, stdev, param))
